{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id6b151dab-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e","identifier":"/us/usc/t33/s59kk"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"59kk"},"text":"§ 59kk.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Wateree River","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For purposes of bridge administration, the portion of the Wateree River in the State of South Carolina, from a point 100 feet upstream of the railroad bridge located at approximately mile marker 10.0 to a point 100 feet downstream of such bridge, is declared to not be navigable waters of the United States for purposes of the General Bridge Act of 1946 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t33/s525"},"text":"33 U.S.C. 525","children":[],"tail":" et seq.)."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id6b17679c-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/293/tVI/s610"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–293, title VI, § 610","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2004-08-09"},"text":"Aug. 9, 2004","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/118/1058"},"text":"118 Stat. 1058","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id6b17679d-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id6b17679e-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id6b17679f-3a70-11f1-9100-cf79f4fb4b3e"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The General Bridge Act of 1946, referred to in text, is title V of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1946-08-02/ch753"},"text":"act Aug. 2, 1946, ch. 753","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/60/847"},"text":"60 Stat. 847","children":[],"tail":", which is classified generally to subchapter III (§ 525 et seq.) of chapter 11 of this title. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t33/s525"},"text":"section 525 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
